1781292057319559	edict-dev	itc:v3:AWLkkmTOfzk5kQAAAAAAQeqtbv7rtAAAAAEvAQ		item.create	bn-659e	{"description":"review.enabled should only gate auto-review (worker/dev auto-request + finish/merge approval gating). Mention hooks for @<project>-<role> should be registered whenever the role is declared in review.reviewers and seal is enabled, so reviewers can be tagged ad-hoc even when auto-review is off. Changes: (1) ensure_reviewer_hooks drops the review.enabled guard, gate on tools.seal; (2) init stops hard-binding enabled=!reviewers.is_empty() as an invariant (keep as default only); (3) migration so downstream projects re-register hooks under the new rule. Motivating case: sigil channel @sigil-security never fired because review.enabled=false suppressed hook registration.","kind":"bug","title":"Decouple reviewer mention-hook registration from review.enabled"}	blake3:6sgyi3iTPZHoa6B71PTxgY6VIg8QWUaeMjy9bYEnnyI
1781292430315532	edict-dev	itc:v3:AWLkkmTOfzk5kQAAAAAAQeqtbv7rtAAAAAEvAg		item.move	bn-659e	{"reason":"Decoupled reviewer mention-hook registration from review.enabled; hooks now gate on seal + declared reviewers. Parity test fixed for root layout. Merged to default.","state":"done"}	blake3:kJCEachRz6EJiQirKeVLbAbMWyUfiLxuLZzryeOIOJc
1781293740546126	edict-dev	itc:v3:AWLkkmTOfzk5kQAAAAAAQeqtbv7rtAAAAAEvAw		item.create	bn-225g	{"description":"When a bare (triage) message @-mentions a configured reviewer (e.g. @sigil-security), the responder also fires (its claim-available hook is a catch-all) and triages the message into dev work, double-spawning alongside the reviewer-loop. rite fires ALL matching hooks by design (confirmed in rite evaluate_hooks_inner), so the responder must self-filter: skip bare messages that mention a configured reviewer. Also add review-request to SKIP_LABELS. Surfaced when tagging @sigil-security also spawned sigil-dev.","kind":"bug","title":"Responder must skip messages directed at reviewers"}	blake3:93gQnbVBDIDjmzAC5qFBZBz6iFWeg2Y_4SJLATXE94A
1781293862995068	edict-dev	itc:v3:AWLkkmTOfzk5kQAAAAAAQeqtbv7rtAAAAAEvBA		item.move	bn-225g	{"reason":"Responder now skips bare triage messages that @-mention a configured reviewer; review-request added to SKIP_LABELS. Tests added. Merged to default.","state":"done"}	blake3:SzX1e0rX7B8FhjY0ikjpNkT_v0iy7sPmkmvzu_SCVGM
1781468044116366	edict-dev	itc:v3:AWLkkmTOfzk5kQAAAAAAQeqtbv7rtAAAAAEvBQ		item.create	bn-2lxr	{"description":"When the responder spawns a dev-loop for a single reported/triaged issue (handle_dev with Some(bone)), the dev-loop drains the whole ready backlog because has_work() returns true for any ready bone and EDICT_MISSION is only an advisory prompt hint. Desired: a focus bone scopes the dev-loop to that bone + its dependency subtree and exits when done; no focus bone keeps the current backlog-draining behavior; honor !dev bn-X to scope explicitly. Implement EDICT_FOCUS env: responder sets it for Focus scope (triage->work, escalation, !dev <bone>); dev-loop reads it, gates has_work on the focus bone's state, exits when done, and the prompt instructs working only that subtree. Missions keep their existing EDICT_MISSION path. User-reported pain: keeps having to vessel kill the dev-loop so it doesn't start unrelated backlog issues.","kind":"bug","title":"Scope dev-loop to focus bone instead of draining backlog"}	blake3:upAHz2bHNKbWgkBiulHdNWR5rE2lys0yIHp-0H_OFy0
1781468625085656	edict-dev	itc:v3:AWLkkmTOfzk5kQAAAAAAQeqtbv7rtAAAAAEvBg		item.move	bn-2lxr	{"reason":"EDICT_FOCUS scoping: responder sets Focus/Backlog/Mission scope; dev-loop works only the focus bone + subtree and exits when done; !dev bn-x honored. Tests added. Merged.","state":"done"}	blake3:mIKmDGoVLUDD52Qn8vvu9PmbLCn-mEEazUgu9D_nInA
1781471260504204	edict-dev	itc:v3:AWLkkmTOfzk5kQAAAAAAQeqtbv7rtAAAAAEvBw		item.create	bn-1ajn	{"description":"Follow-up to bn-2lxr. (1) Missions: unify scope gating so EDICT_MISSION also scopes the loop (work only mission subtree, exit when mission bone done) and the mission prompt instructs not to drain the backlog. (2) Stuck/blocked focus bone: handle_agent_result re-verifies COMPLETE against global has_work, so in scope mode a blocked bone spins to max_loops because the backlog is non-empty. Make handle_agent_result scope-aware: in scope mode, COMPLETE exits (done or stuck) unless workers are still active; END_OF_STORY exits if the scope bone is done. Add a no-progress stall guard: if the scope bone state is unchanged with no active workers for max_idle iterations, exit. Strengthen the focus directive to tell the agent to emit COMPLETE when blocked.","kind":"task","title":"Make dev-loop scope-aware for missions + stuck-bone early exit"}	blake3:Q_fW44xkYcECaGalMKumWQxds3xSDvu3JAGFmQPdRxg
1781471561918654	edict-dev	itc:v3:AWLkkmTOfzk5kQAAAAAAQeqtbv7rtAAAAAEvCA		item.move	bn-1ajn	{"reason":"Missions now scoped via unified EDICT_FOCUS/EDICT_MISSION gate; handle_agent_result scope-aware (COMPLETE exits unless workers active); no-progress stall guard; focus directive instructs COMPLETE when blocked. Tests added. Merged.","state":"done"}	blake3:IiOMVBsoa9jDYKnBJPogKcvlklhjS440eFi1Oze0DZE
